narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: And you thought the way WE dealt with celebrity was weird sometimes.
You study 18th century theater and its applications to modern stardom/celebrity.
I would absolutely recommend this class to another student. It's not a huge time commitment and the discussions are relevant and interesting.
It's not a hard course, and it's really fun if you love pop culture of the past and present.

This is a class that connects current celebrity culture and 18th century celebrity culture. I would recommend it if you are interested in celebrities and the idea of celebrity. It's not too much work, and class time is usually pretty fun and interesting. The readings are kind of random, but always good.

Seminar in pop culture. A mix of intensive theater history of Reformation England and Perez Hilton. I would definitely recommend it, although know that the class is what you make of it--if you put in a lot of effort, you will get a lot out of this class intellectually.
